<br>
Now, as for the BEST soloist, I think Mages and Necros are tied. Druids are 3rd (or second depending on how to look at it) because they cannot solo without Kiting generally, but they are generally the best kiters (my level 40 druid friend can kite 4 spectres at once, sorta impressive)<br>
<br>
As per the Mage vs. Necro debate, I think it depends on how you like to play, like many other posters have said. The Magician is the master of indoor soloing, toe to toe soloing. Magicians are, simply put the closest thing to the best straight fighter there is in Norrath. Your pet is the biggest tank in the game, bigger than a warrior (though no replacement!) able to suck up ungodly amounts of damage. You can damage shield that damage absorber so that while he's absorbing damage he's also dealing it. He has the STRONGEST melee of any pet in the game, and finally you have your direct damage spells, which at any given rank are only second to a Wizard's. If you wanna keep the fight in a small area, the Magician is the best Soloist. <br>
<br>
Outdoors, the Necromancer has the Magician beat. Fear, dots, and his pet, along with his several escape spells of feign death, harm shield, snare, root, screaming terror, and probably many others, allow a Necromancer to easily kill a mob outdoors with a minimum of risk. However this takes a good deal of the control out of a Necromancer's hands. A mob who's escape pathing takes him directly into other hostile mobs will be trouble for the Necromancer. A necro's pet cannot tank for him as well as a Magicians, and many necros spend time running around with a backpack full of weapons to hand to their pet (or ask Magicians for a weapon). His dots and lifetaps are the primary weapon, allowing a necro to suck his life clean and replenish his mana with it, then use that mana at a better efficiency rate than the life -&gt; mana spell to replenish his life, giving a Necromancer an almost unlimited amount of mana, and keep dots on an opponent for a long period of time. If you like a sneaky down and dirty way of fighting (Fear Kiting) and enjoy: <br>
